                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb"><strong>Sixtus Chetachi Igbokwe</strong> is a Nigerian playwright, teacher, and researcher. He holds an MFA in playwriting from the University of Iowa and a BA in English and literary studies from the University of Nigeria, Nsukka. His works have appeared in the <em>Hopkins Review, English Academy Review, Great River Review</em>, and other publications. He won the 2021 Association of Nigerian Authors (ANA) Prize for Drama for his debut play, <em>Homecoming</em>. He is currently a PhD student of theater and performance studies at Stanford University.</p>
